		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Has anyone tried to do a NES programm with the WLA-DX assembler ? Is it better or worse than CA65 ? I personnaly found that both looks really great, and I'm too lazy to compare two 64 pages doccumentation right now <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";-)" title="Wink" /> I guess WLA-DX has the strong point to be compatible with near-every old game machines, so you can change the hardware and using the same assembler.

		

